# Model workflow: Sonnet → develop, Opus → review

## During task development (Sonnet)

All individual task work (T001–T108) must be done using the **Sonnet** model:

- Implementing features, writing migrations, building UI, writing tests
- Running the per-task QA gate (see `qa-after-task` rule)
- Committing per task (see `commit-per-task` rule)
- When using the Task tool for subagents, set `model: "fast"`

## Phase completion review (Opus)

When the **last task in a phase** is marked `done`, stop development and switch to the **Opus** model. Prompt it with:

> "Phase [N] is complete. Run the phase completion review."

### What Opus does

1. **Full audit** — re-read every task's acceptance criteria in the phase and verify each AC is actually met in code
2. **Cross-task integration check** — verify tasks that depend on each other within the phase work together end-to-end
3. **Regression sweep** — run `turbo test` and confirm no regressions from the phase's work
4. **Security & edge-case scan** — review endpoints, permissions, input validation, and error handling across the phase
5. **Code quality review** — check for dead code, inconsistent patterns, missing types, and duplicated logic introduced during the phase
6. **Issue consolidation** — review all issues logged in `docs/issues-tracker.md` during this phase and verify open ones are still valid

### Remediation sub-phase

After the audit, Opus creates a **remediation sub-phase** in `docs/Business/progress.md`:

```
## Phase [N]R — Remediation

| ID      | Task                          | Status  | Source         |
| ------- | ----------------------------- | ------- | -------------- |
| T0XX-R1 | Fix: [description]            | pending | Opus audit     |
| T0XX-R2 | Fix: [description]            | pending | Opus audit     |
| ...     | ...                           | ...     | ...            |
```

- IDs use the format `T0XX-R#` where `XX` is the phase number and `#` is sequential
- Each remediation task must have clear acceptance criteria
- Severity (Critical/High/Medium/Low) must be noted — Critical and High are **blocking**

### Gating rule

- **Do NOT start the next phase** until all Critical and High remediation tasks are `done`
- Medium and Low remediation tasks may be deferred (log them in `docs/issues-tracker.md`)
- Once the remediation sub-phase passes, switch back to **Sonnet** for the next phase's task development
